1- Cluster HTTP con Keepalived

Configurar p√°ginas distintas

	Server1
	echo "<h1>Servidor 1</h1>" | sudo tee /var/www/html/index.html

	Server2
	echo "<h1>Servidor 2</h1>" | sudo tee /var/www/html/index.html

Verifica acceso desde navegador:
	http://192.168.100.140
	http://192.168.100.149

Configurar Keepalived
	Archivo: /etc/keepalived/keepalived.conf
	sudo nano /etc/keepalived/keepalived.conf

server1 (MASTER):
vrrp_instance VI_1 {
    state MASTER
    interface eth0
    virtual_router_id 51
    priority 100
    advert_int 1
    authentication {
        auth_type PASS
        auth_pass 1234
    }
    virtual_ipaddress {
        192.168.1.250/24
    }
}

server2 (BACKUP):
vrrp_instance VI_1 {
    state BACKUP
    interface eth0
    virtual_router_id 51
    priority 90
    advert_int 1
    authentication {
        auth_type PASS
        auth_pass 1234
    }
    virtual_ipaddress {
        192.168.1.250/24
    }
}

Iniciar servicio (ambos servers)
	sudo systemctl enable keepalived
	sudo systemctl start keepalived

Validar HA
	http://192.168.100.250

Apagar el servidor principal:
	sudo systemctl stop keepalived
